0 Whoever wrote the screenplay for this movie obviously never consulted any books about Lucille Ball , especially her autobiography . I 've never seen so many mistakes in a biopic , ranging from her early years in Celoron and Jamestown to her later years with Desi . I could write a whole list of factual errors , but it would go on for pages . In all , I believe that Lucille Ball is one of those inimitable people who simply can not be portrayed by anyone other than themselves . If I were Lucie Arnaz and Desi , Jr. , I would be irate at how many mistakes were made in this film . The filmmakers tried hard , but the movie seems awfully sloppy to me .
