0 Was this meant to be a comedy or a serious drama ? This film starts with a light - hearted banter between three women . Fine . It moves into a conflict between the women when one of them meets a man . Fine . There are a few antics between them . Fine . But when the plot thickens and finally becomes black I started to wonder whether I had misinterpreted the first part of the movie . It continues in this vein for a while until , in the end , it tries to go back to the original light - hearted banter . But by now it 's too late . It 's hard to see why these women would still be talking to one another and the finale is unconvincing . Truly a lesson ( for British filmmakers anyway ) of how not to make films . Difficult to see how the producers ever convinced themselves this film would work . And the box office proved it to be a real flop , because I 'd never heard of this film until this weekend ( four years after its release ) .
